If it&#x27;s a fairly big function, or a common way of dealing with errors in a package you can always define a func (nested or not):<p><pre><code>  func foo() error {
    handleErr = func(err error) bool {
      if err != nil {
         log.Println(err)
         // do other stuff
         return true
      }
      return false
    }
    err := bar()
    if handleErr(err) { return err }
  }
</code></pre>
It&#x27;s nice and concise.

